<config style="display:none"><tags>#01.water on earth</tags><thumbnail></thumbnail><heading></heading><udate>Mon Jul 21 2025 11:26:11 GMT+0600 (Bangladesh Standard Time)</udate><id>article-60tOLqhxD8</id><duration></duration></config><sn><h3>Water on Earth</h3><p>Water is found everywhere on Earth—in the oceans, glaciers, rivers, lakes, air, soil, and living tissue</p><p class="bg-y1"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Earth%27s_water_distribution.svg/1200px-Earth%27s_water_distribution.svg.png" alt="image"></p><ul>
<li class="bg-p1">The vast majority of the water on or close to Earth’s surface (over <code>97</code> percent) is <code>saltwater found in the oceans</code></li>
<li>Much of the remaining <code>3</code> percent is stored in the <code>ice sheets</code> of <code>Antarctica and Greenland</code></li>
<li>Only a meager <code>0.001</code> percent is found in the <code>atmosphere</code>, and most of this is in the form of <code>water vapor</code></li>
